                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3hx1670z/manifest/annotation/p4",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>to leave her again she is expected to visit <placeName>Charleston</placeName><lb/> as\n                soon as she is able to travel &amp; then I will<lb/> give you a more correct\n                statement — Remember<lb/> me kindly to my friends the <persName>Levys</persName>\n                &amp; all who<lb/> remember me. I am now writing without being<lb/> able to see, but\n                I have had so many interruptions<lb/> that I am determined to finish in the\n                dark<lb/> That you may soon be restored to health<lb/> is the sincere wish of your\n                friend</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                <persName role=\"author\">R C Moise</persName>\n            </p>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3hx1670z/canvas/p4"
